{"questionId":"22791","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A ship <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>S</mtext></math> is travelling with a constant velocity, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math>, measured in kilometres per hour, where</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:210px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>15</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>.</p>\n<p>At time <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> the ship is at a point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext><mo>(</mo><mn>300</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>)</mo></math> relative to an origin <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>O</mtext></math>, where distances are&nbsp;measured in kilometres.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A lighthouse is located at a point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>129</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>283</mn><mo>)</mo></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>An alarm will sound if the ship travels within <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn></math> kilometres of the lighthouse.</p>\n<p>State whether the alarm will sound. Give a reason for your answer.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>the alarm will sound&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mover><mtext>LS</mtext><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>19</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>20</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award <em><strong>A1R0</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22791","referenceCode":"21N.1.AHL.TZ0.16c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"An alarm will sound if the ship travels within 20 kilometres of the lighthouse. State whether the alarm will sound. Give a reason for your answer.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.10—Vector definitions","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.11—Vector equation of a line in 2d and 3d","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.12—Vector applications to kinematics","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.13—Scalar and vector products"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}